SIMPLE: lubricity
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lubricity
<hw>Lu*bric"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>lubricitas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>lubricit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Smoothness; freedom from friction; also, property
which diminishes friction; <as>as, the <ex>lubricity</ex> of
oil</as>.</def> <rj><au>Ray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Slipperiness; instability; <as>as, the
<ex>lubricity</ex> of fortune</as>.</def>
<rj><au>L'Estrange.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Lasciviousness; propensity to lewdness; lewdness;
lechery; incontinency.</def> <rj><au>Sir T. Herbert.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As if wantonness and <qex>lubricity</qex> were essential to that
poem.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lubricous</ent>⟦br⟧
